abstract: Labor Dept reports initial claims for state unemployment benefits fell to seasonally adjusted 255,000 for week ended July 18, lowest since 1973; other data offers upbeat picture for United States economy.
lead_paragraph: Other data also offered an upbeat assessment of the economy. A gauge of future economic activity rose in June, and another measure suggested that growth had picked up.

headline.main: New Jobless Claims Fall to 41-Year Low
headline.print_headline: New Claims for Jobless Benefits Fall to a 41-Year Low
